1
00:00:35,250 --> 00:00:40,750
There doesn't exist any human on earth who
can accept our existence the way we are.

2
00:00:41,750 --> 00:00:44,990
The guy you claim to love would be the same.

3
00:00:48,390 --> 00:00:50,100
Hence...

4
00:00:51,100 --> 00:00:53,500
Get a hold of yourself

5
00:00:54,770 --> 00:00:57,070
and never be found out.

6
00:00:58,070 --> 00:00:59,970
Don't come this way, Heo Joon Jae!

7
00:01:18,320 --> 00:01:21,360
You! What are you doing there?

8
00:01:21,360 --> 00:01:23,030
I said don't come this way. Stay away!

9
00:01:23,030 --> 00:01:26,970
Oh, right. Okay, okay, okay. I won't look.

10
00:01:26,970 --> 00:01:28,930
Wait a second. What do you take me for—

11
00:01:28,930 --> 00:01:30,900
I said turn around!

12
00:01:34,010 --> 00:01:35,910
- Hey. - Don't turn around!

13
00:01:35,910 --> 00:01:37,740
I said I won't look.

14
00:01:39,040 --> 00:01:41,580
Hey, what I told you was to clean the house.

15
00:01:41,610 --> 00:01:45,720
When did I tell you to get in the
water and play around? Seriously...

16
00:01:45,750 --> 00:01:47,420
Don't turn around! Don't turn around!

17
00:01:47,420 --> 00:01:49,350
Ah, I'm only trying to shut the door. Just the door!

18
00:01:49,350 --> 00:01:52,020
The-the-the door. Don't shut the door.
Don't shut the door.

19
00:01:52,020 --> 00:01:53,490
Gawd, what will you have me do?

20
00:01:53,490 --> 00:01:56,260
Nothing! Don't do anything!

21
00:01:58,960 --> 00:02:01,570
- Let me just as you one question.- Don't even ask.

22
00:02:10,980 --> 00:02:12,810
I'm all done.

23
00:02:16,380 --> 00:02:18,320
What is all done?

24
00:02:18,320 --> 00:02:20,450
What's the one question you had?

25
00:02:21,450 --> 00:02:22,790
Huh?

26
00:02:23,790 --> 00:02:25,920
Ah, right...

27
00:02:29,130 --> 00:02:36,800
Should you or shouldn't you be so careless
in a house full of men like that...

28
00:02:36,870 --> 00:02:39,270
I didn't anticipate your sudden return.

29
00:02:39,270 --> 00:02:43,280
Should you or shouldn't you return home
so suddenly after you leave the house?

30
00:02:47,410 --> 00:02:51,450
It's MY house. This house exists so that I can

31
00:02:51,450 --> 00:02:53,720
go out and return suddenly as I see fit.
This house right here.

32
00:02:53,720 --> 00:02:57,460
Should the burden of care that one
must take fall on you or on me?

33
00:02:57,460 --> 00:03:00,990
- On you.  - Not true. It should be on you!

34
00:03:00,990 --> 00:03:04,030
To put it bluntly,
you are really lucky because it was me.

35
00:03:04,030 --> 00:03:08,330
Just imagine what you would have done, if
this happened when the other punks were here.

36
00:03:08,330 --> 00:03:11,400
- What makes you the lucky option?  - Because I...

37
00:03:15,870 --> 00:03:20,550
Are you engaging in a repartee with me?
Quickly go and change your clothes.

38
00:03:20,550 --> 00:03:22,650
I can only dress when you leave.

39
00:03:24,450 --> 00:03:26,050
Right?

40
00:03:43,070 --> 00:03:45,040
Episode 8

41
00:03:45,040 --> 00:03:46,640
What took you so long?

42
00:03:46,640 --> 00:03:48,970
- Huh?- What about your cell phone? Did you get it?

43
00:03:50,240 --> 00:03:52,310
- I'll just go.- You'll just go?

44
00:03:52,310 --> 00:03:54,550
It's okay. Let's just go.

45
00:03:58,350 --> 00:03:59,890
Ah, wait, wait a minute.

46
00:03:59,890 --> 00:04:02,720
I have an announcement to make...

47
00:04:02,720 --> 00:04:06,990
From now on, when you return home, ring the
door bell at least once before you enter.

48
00:04:07,990 --> 00:04:10,230
- What's the reason? - I'll be doing the same. I will.

49
00:04:10,230 --> 00:04:12,460
So, ring the door bell before you enter.

50
00:04:12,460 --> 00:04:15,030
Make some noise to announce
your presence once as well.

51
00:04:15,030 --> 00:04:16,940
So I'm asking as to WHY do we have to do this?

52
00:04:16,940 --> 00:04:20,940
Geez, why do you question the request
the owner of the house is making?

53
00:04:20,940 --> 00:04:22,390
As for you Tae Oh.

54
00:04:22,390 --> 00:04:25,910
Don't you enter by silently picking the
lock and stuff. I'm telling you to watch it.

55
00:04:25,910 --> 00:04:28,950
- What nonsense... - You'd better watch it!

56
00:04:28,950 --> 00:04:31,480
Why is it...so hot?

57
00:04:31,480 --> 00:04:32,880
- Hot you say? - Aren't you?

58
00:04:32,880 --> 00:04:35,450
- They say it's below freezing. - It's so oddly hot.

59
00:04:35,450 --> 00:04:37,720
As you say, your face is red.

60
00:04:42,530 --> 00:04:44,460
You mean you were almost found out?

61
00:04:45,260 --> 00:04:49,270
It could have been a big problem.
I told you to be careful.

62
00:04:49,270 --> 00:04:50,590
From his perspective,
he'll continue to poke around

63
00:04:50,650 --> 00:04:54,110
and question this and that since you're
suspicious, telling you to fess up your secret.

64
00:04:54,110 --> 00:04:55,640
He's already doing that now.

65
00:04:55,640 --> 00:04:59,780
"What happened in Spain? Why can't I
remember? If you won't say, get out."

66
00:04:59,780 --> 00:05:02,090
You can't get sucked into
that strategy and fess up.

67
00:05:02,090 --> 00:05:04,020
You can never be "mermaiding out."
(Like coming out)

68
00:05:04,020 --> 00:05:06,850
Uhm. Never will I be "mermaiding out."

69
00:05:06,850 --> 00:05:11,190
What little consolation that a
thing called "lie" exists here.

70
00:05:11,190 --> 00:05:13,090
Would that have worked in our neck of the woods?

71
00:05:13,090 --> 00:05:14,600
You know that as soon as I think of something,

72
00:05:14,600 --> 00:05:18,100
everyone within 10Km radius
knows everything in my heart.

73
00:05:18,100 --> 00:05:18,930
True.

74
00:05:18,930 --> 00:05:24,800
At least here, we can hide our real feelings
with a lie since they can't hear our thoughts.

75
00:05:24,800 --> 00:05:27,070
Do people really lie so much?

76
00:05:27,070 --> 00:05:31,480
Not only do they lie a lot, but they
lie every time they open their mouths.

77
00:05:31,480 --> 00:05:33,910
Have you mastered Hangeul (Korean alphabet)?

78
00:05:34,910 --> 00:05:36,350
Then what does it say there.Free
phone 100%... The boss is crazy!

79
00:05:36,350 --> 00:05:39,320
Free phone 100%... The boss is crazy!

80
00:05:39,320 --> 00:05:42,020
Do you suppose that statement is true,
and it means that the boss is crazy?

81
00:05:42,020 --> 00:05:44,720
- That's not what it means?  - No, of course it isn't.

82
00:05:45,720 --> 00:05:47,960
Since we'll recoup the cost
using any means necessary,

83
00:05:47,960 --> 00:05:51,460
all you need to do is come and spend
your money. That's what it means.

84
00:05:51,460 --> 00:05:52,760
Ah, is that what it means?

85
00:05:52,760 --> 00:05:54,470
When you go to the department
stores, the employees

86
00:05:54,470 --> 00:05:58,500
always tell you, "This attire suits you perfectly.
It was made for you!" no matter what you wear, right?

87
00:05:58,500 --> 00:05:59,740
Do you know what it means?

88
00:05:59,740 --> 00:06:01,810
- Doesn't that mean it looks pretty?  - Come now.

89
00:06:01,810 --> 00:06:03,760
- (It means) since I gave you
the lip-service (compliment)

90
00:06:03,760 --> 00:06:07,780
you ought to be a mensch and buy something.

91
00:06:08,780 --> 00:06:10,750
And this is the important point.

92
00:06:10,750 --> 00:06:13,850
In this place, the word "love" is very common.

93
00:06:13,850 --> 00:06:18,560
But you can't be deceived by that.
It doesn't mean (they) really love you.

94
00:06:18,560 --> 00:06:20,090
Want to see?

95
00:06:25,700 --> 00:06:27,300
I love you, Dear Customer~

96
00:06:27,300 --> 00:06:29,030
I'm sorry.

97
00:06:31,970 --> 00:06:34,050
Just because someone said
"I love you" to you, if you suggest, "Shall we date?"

98
00:06:34,050 --> 00:06:36,240
then you'll have a major problem.

99
00:06:36,240 --> 00:06:38,110
You will be shackled.

100
00:06:38,110 --> 00:06:40,010
It's difficult.

101
00:06:40,010 --> 00:06:42,450
Then how can you tell when
people are lying to you?

102
00:06:42,450 --> 00:06:43,980
It's not easy.

103
00:06:43,980 --> 00:06:47,820
One of the methods I've found thus far is...

104
00:06:47,820 --> 00:06:52,260
people who lie either can't meet your eye,

105
00:06:52,260 --> 00:06:55,460
stutter, or touch their ears.

106
00:06:55,460 --> 00:07:01,230
At times they touch their lips or cross
their arms to take a defensive posture.

107
00:07:02,230 --> 00:07:05,640
What do you mean? How do I notice Cheong?

108
00:07:05,640 --> 00:07:08,470
Not true? You seem to care a
lot about Cheong these days.

109
00:07:08,470 --> 00:07:10,410
To-ho-tally not at all.

110
00:07:10,410 --> 00:07:12,940
Honestly, this is the first time
I've seen you do that to a woman.

111
00:07:12,940 --> 00:07:15,210
Demanding a dress code
(length of skirt, skin showing).

112
00:07:16,110 --> 00:07:19,480
Ah, come on. You know I had
given you the dress code too.

113
00:07:19,480 --> 00:07:22,550
Furthermore, I pay attention
to Tae Oh's clothes too.

114
00:07:22,550 --> 00:07:24,620
Hey, how come do you dress so thinly these days?

115
00:07:24,620 --> 00:07:26,220
Shall I buy you a parka?

116
00:07:27,090 --> 00:07:31,000
- I don't quite think that's it. - That is it.

117
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:33,530
- Just drop me off right up there.
- Why? Don't you want to go together?

118
00:07:33,530 --> 00:07:35,400
You agreed to check out the
gallery for our work together.

119
00:07:35,400 --> 00:07:39,200
Can't the two of you just go together by now?

120
00:07:39,200 --> 00:07:41,110
I have some other matter to take care of.

121
00:07:41,110 --> 00:07:43,140
Why? To meet with Si Ah?

122
00:07:50,580 --> 00:07:53,920
What a pleasant surprise without
even calling ahead? What's up?

123
00:07:53,920 --> 00:07:56,240
You told me last time that a
several hundred-year-old shipwreck

124
00:07:56,240 --> 00:07:59,560
was discovered in the Yangyang ocean.

125
00:07:59,560 --> 00:08:03,260
You remembered it despite the
appearance of partially listening to it.

126
00:08:03,260 --> 00:08:07,370
Nam Doo Hyung told me yesterday
that its mokgan was discovered.

127
00:08:07,370 --> 00:08:10,970
That's right. That's why my research
office is in such an uproar.

128
00:08:10,970 --> 00:08:14,410
And the... name of owner of the items is...

129
00:08:14,410 --> 00:08:16,410
Kim Dam Ryeong.

130
00:08:16,410 --> 00:08:20,210
He was the chief of the village
of Heupgok named Kim Dam Ryeong.

131
00:08:20,210 --> 00:08:22,430
(Mokgan: a small wooden
panel that recorded the ship's origin,

132
00:08:22,430 --> 00:08:24,580
destination, and purpose of the journey)

133
00:08:25,820 --> 00:08:27,820
This is the item.

134
00:08:27,850 --> 00:08:33,460
Just by looking at the year inscribed on the
mokgan, it is certainly a mid-Joseon era item,

135
00:08:33,460 --> 00:08:35,930
but look at the clothes the male is wearing.

136
00:08:35,930 --> 00:08:40,130
They match modern day clothing as if
it were drawn with the future in mind.

137
00:08:41,030 --> 00:08:45,240
In addition, isn't it truly
mystical to see a mermaid?

138
00:08:45,240 --> 00:08:46,970
It's as you say.

139
00:09:13,070 --> 00:09:16,300
Legend of the Blue Sea

140
00:09:17,870 --> 00:09:21,270
Lately, it's been strange.

141
00:09:21,270 --> 00:09:24,710
Not to mention having a
strange, repeating dream...

142
00:09:24,710 --> 00:09:27,580
When I was looking at the
illustration on that vase...

143
00:09:29,880 --> 00:09:33,890
Gosh, this might really sound crazy, but

144
00:09:33,890 --> 00:09:38,560
I felt like the male in the
illustration was definitely me.

145
00:09:39,460 --> 00:09:42,360
It isn't as if I recall anything.

146
00:09:42,360 --> 00:09:45,030
I've done a fair amount of clinical
experiments and such to bring about

147
00:09:45,030 --> 00:09:49,000
a short-term memory loss via brief
cognitive hypnosis, but this is different.

148
00:09:49,000 --> 00:09:55,410
It's as if only a specific portion of
my memory of being in Spain was erased.

149
00:09:56,310 --> 00:09:59,180
Is this type of thing possible, Professor?

150
00:09:59,180 --> 00:10:02,350
Well, dissociative phenomena is,

151
00:10:02,350 --> 00:10:06,750
in the end, an issue of separation (dissociation),
so I can't say that it is completely impossible.

152
00:10:06,820 --> 00:10:11,090
An episodic amnesia can
sporadically happen as well.

153
00:10:11,120 --> 00:10:15,730
(Chae Gye Sung amnesia: memory loss
specific to an event or a person)

154
00:10:20,400 --> 00:10:25,340
Now your memory for that person

155
00:10:25,340 --> 00:10:30,710
will go back where it started.

156
00:10:53,070 --> 00:10:58,100
Are you okay, Joon Jae?
What did you see? Do you remember?

157
00:10:58,100 --> 00:10:59,100
Professor Park.

158
00:10:59,100 --> 00:11:03,710
Yes, Joon Jae. Tell me everything you saw.

159
00:11:03,710 --> 00:11:06,650
Professor told me before

160
00:11:08,180 --> 00:11:12,880
that hypnosis can bring out my subconscious

161
00:11:12,880 --> 00:11:16,120
but can also possibly bring out illusion.

162
00:11:16,120 --> 00:11:17,260
I said so.

163
00:11:17,260 --> 00:11:23,360
I think that's what I see, the illusion.

164
00:11:24,060 --> 00:11:25,900
Otherwise,

165
00:11:28,470 --> 00:11:30,200
this doesn't make sense.

166
00:11:35,970 --> 00:11:38,240
Whoa, you're the best player in the whole country?

167
00:11:38,240 --> 00:11:41,210
Not just within your guild,
but in the whole country?

168
00:11:48,320 --> 00:11:50,060
Heo Joon Jae!

169
00:11:51,290 --> 00:11:53,230
- Are you going somewhere?- Yes, I—

170
00:11:53,230 --> 00:11:57,230
Never mind. I don't need to know. Please go ahead.

171
00:11:57,230 --> 00:11:59,430
Alright.

172
00:11:59,430 --> 00:12:03,800
But... Starting today, we have a curfew.

173
00:12:03,800 --> 00:12:06,840
- We do? - Yes, starting today.

174
00:12:06,840 --> 00:12:09,270
What time?

175
00:12:09,270 --> 00:12:13,650
Eight PM. Come back by eight, or else we'll
lock the door and won't let you back in.

176
00:12:13,650 --> 00:12:15,250
Hey, it's 7:30.

177
00:12:15,250 --> 00:12:17,920
That's what I mean. She needs to come back by eight.

178
00:12:17,920 --> 00:12:20,720
Where in Seoul would she go if
she needs to come back in 30 mins?

179
00:12:20,720 --> 00:12:22,420
You might as well tell her not to go.

180
00:12:22,420 --> 00:12:24,690
Who's telling her not to go?

181
00:12:24,690 --> 00:12:28,790
Go. I don't know with whom she's meeting up.

182
00:12:28,790 --> 00:12:31,030
Anyway, whoever that guy...

183
00:12:32,160 --> 00:12:35,500
Wait, I don't even know if
she's meeting a guy or a girl.

184
00:12:35,500 --> 00:12:39,070
Anyway, after she meets whomever
that unknown person may be,

185
00:12:39,070 --> 00:12:41,170
she needs to come back by eight.

186
00:12:41,170 --> 00:12:42,380
If she doesn't like it, she can
simply stay away from here permanently.

187
00:12:42,380 --> 00:12:43,980
The 7th Level Civil Servant Breaking Through

188
00:12:44,780 --> 00:12:49,680
Whose book is this? The 7th Grade Civil Servant?

189
00:12:49,680 --> 00:12:52,020
- Are you trying to become a civil
servant?- Are you in your right mind?

190
00:12:52,020 --> 00:12:55,350
I was just reading it,
thinking it might help with our work.

191
00:12:55,350 --> 00:12:57,720
It's what kind of study people do these days.

192
00:12:57,720 --> 00:13:01,730
I was curious. As a matter of analyzing a trend.

193
00:13:02,960 --> 00:13:05,060
Are you going out?

194
00:13:05,060 --> 00:13:09,470
No, I won't. I'll just go out tomorrow.

195
00:13:10,840 --> 00:13:14,670
Well, then.

196
00:13:17,840 --> 00:13:21,250
He's strange, really.

197
00:13:21,250 --> 00:13:23,720
Where were you going to go at this hour, my Cheong?

198
00:13:23,720 --> 00:13:27,150
- I was going out to make money.- Making
money? You mean doing a part-time work?

199
00:13:27,150 --> 00:13:30,920
No, I was going to exchange these for money.

200
00:13:30,920 --> 00:13:34,090
After exchanging them, I was going to
give all the money to Heo Joon Jae.

201
00:13:34,090 --> 00:13:36,730
What are these?

202
00:13:41,470 --> 00:13:43,100
Oh, these...

203
00:13:48,840 --> 00:13:50,640
Where did you get them?

204
00:13:50,640 --> 00:13:53,210
I got them by working hard.

205
00:14:10,360 --> 00:14:14,200
What kind of work do you need to do
to get these high-quality pearls?

206
00:14:14,200 --> 00:14:17,020
You've become even more mysterious.

207
00:14:17,020 --> 00:14:19,300
You need to appear on
an investigation program, "Tell Me the Truth".

208
00:14:19,300 --> 00:14:22,610
- Can you give me one of these?- No.

209
00:14:22,610 --> 00:14:25,180
I get it, I get it. I'll just look.

210
00:14:27,080 --> 00:14:30,880
Whoa, these are of really high quality.

211
00:14:30,880 --> 00:14:33,820
I have finished cooking yummy white rice.

212
00:14:33,820 --> 00:14:37,020
Are you sure? Have you finished it for sure?

213
00:14:37,020 --> 00:14:39,020
Good job, really.

214
00:14:43,430 --> 00:14:45,500
Rice Cheong, Rice Cheong!

215
00:14:45,500 --> 00:14:48,370
She's not Sim Cheong, but Rice Cheong!

216
00:15:01,980 --> 00:15:03,720
Are you hurt?

217
00:15:09,120 --> 00:15:15,590
Do you know why I work as a
life guard in this cold weather?

218
00:15:15,590 --> 00:15:17,000
You don't have a place to sleep?

219
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:21,270
Hey, I rent a 30 Pyeong (100 sqm /1000 sqft)
apartment near Omokgyo subway station.

220
00:15:21,270 --> 00:15:22,400
I make a decent living.

221
00:15:22,400 --> 00:15:25,700
I also have a king-sized bed, a big one.

222
00:15:25,700 --> 00:15:29,780
- Do you know why I'm here after all? - Why?

223
00:15:29,780 --> 00:15:33,950
My heart has almost reached its limit.

224
00:15:35,910 --> 00:15:40,950
I have to be in the water for a
few hours a day to survive the day.

225
00:15:40,950 --> 00:15:44,090
Of course, I don't even know
when it will stop working.

226
00:15:44,090 --> 00:15:49,160
- What do you do then?
Do you have any other way?- There is.

227
00:15:49,160 --> 00:15:53,770
My love has to come back to me, but it won't work.

228
00:15:53,770 --> 00:15:56,030
She's married to another guy.

229
00:15:56,030 --> 00:15:59,600
Then quickly go back to the sea.
What are you doing here?

230
00:15:59,600 --> 00:16:02,340
Look who's talking? What are you doing here?

231
00:16:02,340 --> 00:16:06,510
If you had to erase his memory as
you were caught while saving him,

232
00:16:06,510 --> 00:16:11,180
then you should just consider that a good
memory and go back to the sea where you live.

233
00:16:11,180 --> 00:16:13,850
Who appreciates you for
keeping a forgotten promise?

234
00:16:13,850 --> 00:16:17,620
Why did you come all the way here? For what?

235
00:16:17,620 --> 00:16:20,880
To endure all the suspicion
and mistreatment to the extent of abuse?

236
00:16:20,880 --> 00:16:23,530
And wonder when he'll love you?

237
00:16:24,230 --> 00:16:27,030
You go back quickly when you still have a chance.

238
