The mermaid princess looked
at the prince once more

504
00:39:23,580 --> 00:39:26,580
and threw her body in the sea.

505
00:39:26,580 --> 00:39:30,820
And she felt her body turn into sea foam.

506
00:39:36,690 --> 00:39:40,790
Don't worry too much. He will wake up soon.

507
00:39:40,790 --> 00:39:41,930
Thank you.

508
00:39:41,930 --> 00:39:47,170
But then, no matter how I think about it, he
is not a person who would drink and drive.

509
00:39:47,170 --> 00:39:49,170
That's what I am saying!

510
00:39:49,170 --> 00:39:51,670
Can the black box not be recovered?

511
00:39:51,670 --> 00:39:53,740
Yes, they said it could not.

512
00:39:53,740 --> 00:39:55,740
You can't find his cellphone, either?

513
00:39:55,740 --> 00:40:00,810
Oh, but the phone is under my name,

514
00:40:00,810 --> 00:40:06,520
so I got all the records. But there was
nothing special before the accident.

515
00:40:06,520 --> 00:40:09,720
This, can I take this?

516
00:40:09,720 --> 00:40:10,960
I will look into it.

517
00:40:10,960 --> 00:40:12,260
Will you please do so?

518
00:40:12,260 --> 00:40:15,860
Among my friends, there are detectives
and prosecutors. I will ask around.

519
00:40:15,860 --> 00:40:18,000
Thank you so much.

520
00:40:18,000 --> 00:40:22,030
The madam told me not to
make things pointlessly big.

521
00:40:22,030 --> 00:40:25,500
I had nowhere to ask.

522
00:40:25,500 --> 00:40:28,470
Don't worry so much.

523
00:40:28,470 --> 00:40:30,540
Thank you.

524
00:40:39,920 --> 00:40:42,190
Joon Jae, later at 7...

525
00:40:42,190 --> 00:40:46,960
Let's meet at Yeonheung-Dong 29-21.
I'll wait for you.

526
00:40:46,960 --> 00:40:50,830
- Let's go. I'll take you home.-
No, I will go and meet my friend.

527
00:40:50,830 --> 00:40:54,270
Who? That civil servant?

528
00:40:54,270 --> 00:40:58,000
You, don't forget your curfew. Hurry and go home.

529
00:40:58,000 --> 00:41:00,670
If not, I will kick you out.

530
00:41:02,470 --> 00:41:05,840
It's eight! Okay?

531
00:41:11,280 --> 00:41:14,620
- Honey.  - Honey, what brings you here suddenly?

532
00:41:14,620 --> 00:41:17,690
I was nearby for some business,

533
00:41:17,690 --> 00:41:21,730
and I came to eat with you
if you didn't have any plans.

534
00:41:21,730 --> 00:41:26,200
Is that so? What should we do?
I have a prior appointment.

535
00:41:26,200 --> 00:41:28,830
Is that so? What is it?

536
00:41:28,830 --> 00:41:32,040
It's just a year-end party.

537
00:41:33,140 --> 00:41:35,170
I see.

538
00:41:35,170 --> 00:41:38,880
It's okay. It's not like I came
having plans with you already.

539
00:41:38,880 --> 00:41:40,880
Wait.

540
00:41:41,850 --> 00:41:46,350
- Yes, I was just leaving now.
- Chairman, I am so sorry.

541
00:41:46,350 --> 00:41:51,260
Something urgent happened at home.
Can we set another date for this?

542
00:41:51,260 --> 00:41:54,330
Okay. We can't do anything about that. Okay.

543
00:41:56,290 --> 00:41:59,500
We can eat dinner together.
My appointment just got canceled.

544
00:41:59,500 --> 00:42:02,800
Oh, my. That turned out well.

545
00:42:02,800 --> 00:42:07,470
Honey, should we call Chi Hyeon so
we can have a cozy meal together?

546
00:42:07,470 --> 00:42:09,710
Sure.

547
00:42:14,510 --> 00:42:15,780
Who are you?

548
00:42:15,780 --> 00:42:18,480
Is Yoo Jeong Hoon here? He's my friend?

549
00:42:18,480 --> 00:42:21,920
- Are you perhaps, Kim Hye Jin?
- No, my name is Sim Cheong.

550
00:42:21,920 --> 00:42:25,760
- Ah, is that so?  - Why is he not here today?

551
00:42:25,760 --> 00:42:31,060
The truth is, that friend while saving a person
who fell in Han River a few days ago at dawn,

552
00:42:31,060 --> 00:42:38,370
had a sudden heart attack. When he was
moved to the hospital, he was already dead.

553
00:42:46,310 --> 00:42:49,880
Excuse me, are you perhaps
the person who called me?

554
00:42:49,880 --> 00:42:53,820
- I am Kim Hye Jin. - Yes, I called you.

555
00:42:53,820 --> 00:42:59,090
That person, what happened to him?

556
00:42:59,090 --> 00:43:01,690
He died, you said?

557
00:43:01,690 --> 00:43:04,200
I'm sorry.

558
00:43:04,200 --> 00:43:09,200
That punk must have known something would
happen to him. I don't know how he knew.

559
00:43:09,200 --> 00:43:14,140
He left this in his drawer
with your contact info.

560
00:43:30,290 --> 00:43:33,290
Pink tinged? The one that comes
out when you're really happy?

561
00:43:33,290 --> 00:43:35,330
That's right.

562
00:43:35,330 --> 00:43:39,700
But then, when you stay here,
there aren't that many things that happen

563
00:43:39,700 --> 00:43:45,570
that would make you cry out of happiness.
I only cried like that once.

564
00:43:45,570 --> 00:43:51,880
While he stayed here,
he cried out of happiness only once.

565
00:43:54,650 --> 00:43:59,890
He said he was so happy that
he cried because of you.

566
00:43:59,890 --> 00:44:05,890
All those happy times,
he must have wanted to leave it here.

567
00:44:17,440 --> 00:44:23,310
I didn't know he had a friend
he could tell these things to.

568
00:44:23,310 --> 00:44:26,650
He was filled with so many secrets with me.

569
00:44:26,650 --> 00:44:29,280
Did you leave him because
you detested the secrets?

570
00:44:29,280 --> 00:44:33,190
Secrets are made because people are different,

571
00:44:33,190 --> 00:44:37,320
because you would have to not
get caught being different.

572
00:44:37,320 --> 00:44:42,330
That's why that secret, in the
end, gives each other wounds.

573
00:44:42,330 --> 00:44:46,260
Both the person who is hiding something
and the person it is being hidden from...

574
00:44:46,260 --> 00:44:48,630
They all get hurt.

575
00:44:49,970 --> 00:44:53,070
That's why, if they are both different...

576
00:44:53,070 --> 00:44:56,410
In the end, they can't go together.

577
00:44:56,410 --> 00:44:58,480
You can't go together if you are different?

578
00:44:58,480 --> 00:45:04,050
Anyway, you know that you would
only be giving pain to the other.

579
00:45:04,050 --> 00:45:09,190
Would you be able to go together just
for the reason that you love that person?

580
00:45:12,060 --> 00:45:15,460
Jeong Hoon told me he doesn't regret it.

581
00:45:17,230 --> 00:45:24,300
Because it's a heart that beats for only one
person, even if it hardens and dies in the end,

582
00:45:24,300 --> 00:45:27,970
